graph.guideContent11: 1. In a computational graph display area, you can view a computational graph, zoom in or out a computational graph by scrolling the mouse wheel, and drag a computational graph.
graph.guideContent12: 2. A computational graph can be displayed in full screen or saved as an SVG file.
graph.guideContent13: 3. In the function area on the right, you can switch to view computational graphs of different files or search for nodes in a computational graph.
graph.guideContent14: 4. In the node information, you can click an input or output node to go to the selected node.
graph.guideContent2: Node types of a computational graph include namespace node, operator node, virtual node,   aggregation node, and constant node. "Default" indicates forward propagation, and "Gradients" indicates backward propagation.
graph.guideContent3: Data edges and control edges exist in a computational graph. A data edge indicates the data input, and a control edge indicates the execution dependency between node.

common-profiler_tutorial.desc: How Do I Use Profiler for Profiling?

step_trace-iter_interval.desc: After the praph mode and dataset sink mode are enabled, if the average step interval is greater than {n1} ms, the process from data processing to computational graph execution can be optimized.

minddata_pipeline-general.desc: The {n1} operator in the pipeline may have performance bottlenecks.

minddata_pipeline-dataset_op.desc: For operator {n1}, you can adjust the num_parallel_workers parameter.

minddata_pipeline-generator_op.desc: For operator {n1}, you can adjust the num_parallel_workers parameter or optimize the training script. If the performance is not optimized, you can replace the operator with the MindRecordDataset operator.

minddata_pipeline-map_op.desc: For operator {n1}, you can adjust the num_parallel_workers parameter. If the Python operator is used, you can optimize the training script.

minddata_pipeline-batch_op.desc: For operator {n1}, you can increase the prefetch_size value.

minddata_warning_op.desc: Based on the preceding determination, the operator {n1} can be optimized.

minddata_device_queue.desc: The ratio of empty queues on a host is {n1}/{n2}, and the ratio of full queues is {n3}/{n4}.

minddata_get_next_queue.desc: The ratio of empty queues on a chip is {n1}/{n2}.

profiling.pipelineTopTitle: Average usage of queues between operators
profiling.iterationInfo: The step trace displays the duration of each step from the start of the previous iteration to the end of the step. The main time is divided into three parts: step interval, forward and backward propagation, and step tail.
profiling.iterationGapInfo: Reads data from data queues. If this part takes a long time, you are advised to check the data processing for further analysis.
profiling.fpbpInfo: Executes the forward and backward operators on the network, which carry the main calculation work of a step. If this part takes a long time, you are advised to check the operator statistics or timeline for further analysis.
profiling.iterativeTailingInfo: Performs parameter aggregation and update operations in multi-card scenarios. If the operations take a long time,you are advised to check the time consumed by all_reduce and the parallel status.
profiling.fpbpTimeRatio: Ratio of time consumed by forward and backward propagation:
profiling.iterationGapTimeRatio: Ratio of time consumed by step interval:
profiling.iterativeTailingTimeRatio: Ratio of time consumed by step tail:
profiling.dataProcess: This shows the data processing. Data is stored in the host queue during data processing, and then stored in the data queue on a chip during data transmission. Finally, the forward and backward propagation get_next transmits the data to forward propagation.
profiling.dataProcessInfo: By determining the empty host and data queues, you can preliminarily determine the stage where the performance is abnormal.
profiling.analysisOne: 1. If the step interval is long and some batches of the data queue on a chip are empty, the performance is abnormal during data processing and transmission. Otherwise, locate the internal problem of the forward and backward propagation get_next.
profiling.analysisTwo: 2. If the performance is abnormal during data processing and transmission, check the host queue. If the host queue is empty at a high probability, the exception may occur during data transmission.
profiling.higherAnalysis: Note: You can perform advanced analysis based on the time consumed by operators.
profiling.chipInfo: Ratio of empty data queues on a chip:
profiling.hostIsEmpty: Ratio of empty queues on a host:
profiling.hostIsFull: Ratio of full queues on a host:

timelineTips.content12: - Flow tiling policy of MindSpore on the network.
timelineTips.content13: - Execution sequence and duration of an operator on a device.

timelineTips.content31: You can analyze whether the flow tiling policy is proper and whether the step interval and tail time are too long based on the timeline information.
